description:
&lt;p&gt;Circle Bath (Private Healthcare Provider) is growing and we have exciting opportunities for Registered Nurses to join our In- Patient Unit Team. We first opened our doors in March 2010. Designed by renowned architect Sir Norman Foster, this award-winning private hospital offers both inpatient and outpatient care in a unique setting overlooking the Wiltshire countryside. With a chef trained at Michelin-starred establishments, staff trained in hospitality and excellent clinical care, Circle Bath was a pioneer in developing hospitals that feel more like a hotel. In 2014, it was ranked among the highest-scoring hospitals for patient-reported outcomes in hip and knee surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Inpatient Unit is a stylish 28 bedded modern environment, offering pre and post-operative care for a wide range of elective surgical procedures. We are looking for Registered Nurses who are compassionate, enthusiastic, highly motivated and looking for a challenge. You must possess excellent communication skills, be committed to delivering high standards of care, we offer professional development and a modern, stylish alternative environment to work in, with a different pace and a small friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit is open 7 days per week with Theatre lists running Monday to Saturday. A combination of shifts patterns are available. Free Uniforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent Contracts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible working hours, shift patterns include, early, late, long day and nights&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Person Specification:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•NMC registration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Demonstrable record of CPD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Knowledge of current issues in professional practice •Surgical ward nursing experience is desirable but not essential Newly qualified Nurses welcome to apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Free Parking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Travel to Work Bus, Cycle schemes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Childcare Vouchers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•27 days annual leave with additional days after qualifying period (pro-rata for part timers)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Health and Well Being programme which includes free fruit, massages and fitness sessions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Employee Assistance Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Discounted food from the Atrium Café&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Private Medical Assurance after qualifying period&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Non-contributory Life Assurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
